29 SUMMARY
3300 This amendment clarifies that when a completed marriage license is returned more than
3311 15 working days after the date of solemnization, it must be marked as a late filing. The
3322 amendment also specifies that when the parties to a marriage apply for a certificate of
3333 marriage for a marriage that occurred more than one year previously but for which no
3344 record can be found, it must be marked as a delayed marriage registration.
